  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Bring the steak to room temperature.  Cook the chips in the air fryer or oven following pack instructions."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pick the parsley leaves from their stalks and finely chop. Peel and finely chop the garlic. On the chopping board, mix the parsley, garlic, oregano and red pepper flakes together. Transfer to a bowl and stir through almost all of the olive oil and red wine vinegar. Season with salt and pepper to taste — that’s your chimichurri done."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Boil the eggs for 7 mins (for jammy centres), then run under cold water until cool enough to peel."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, set a heavy-duty nonstick frying pan over a medium-high heat. Brush the steak with the remaining oil and season well with salt and pepper. Once hot, add the steak and cook for 2 to 2½ mins each side for medium-rare. Remove from the pan and leave to rest, then slice."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dish out the chips, and the sliced steak. Cut the eggs in half, then drizzle over the chimichurri sauce to serve."
    }
  ],
